content: Very enjoyable and charming little game to pass the time. Nice graphics and sound.

Love LillithGames animation style! Sometimes a bit difficult to figure out how to get what you want, but worth getting to the next scene for the reward of the scenic art as well. Warning (spoiler alert): A little gory at the end of the whale scene.
Nice game bro!

This game is great! The graphics are really cool and the clues are clever. I would recommend this game to anyone who would like to spend a few hours absorbed in a game. Played a year later. Game finished before i found all the clues.
Its a rip off 79p for a hint its cost me 1.40p just for 2 hints. The watch videos for hints are unhelpfull and vague . DONT BUY,DONT BUY DONT BUY other 2nd game the hints are 89p its a con KEEP CLEAR

The game would be great except for two infuriatingly unfair puzzles. One puzzle is hidden and you can't even find it without random pixel hunting, and another depends on clues hidden in a separate menu outside of the actual game environment. Not fair. Don't waste your time.
Was looking forward to it, but doesnt open...black screen :(
Absolutely amazing, very fun and challenging, loved the art and puzzles. Great work!

The relation of the puzzles in the game are not always clear. You must play through twice to get the real ending, repeating puzzles you already did, and even then there are some puzzles that can only be solved by nonsensical clicking through about / credits. Some areas you need to interact with have no indication there is anything noticable.
Love it! The artwork is beautiful and the music matches it perfectly, It's got fun little puzzles that aren't too stressful and the story makes you question how we got here. Great job! üòÅ
Interesting game and love that it is a repeater to fully enjoy the game

Was initially really fun, solving problems using clues littered all over the island. Later multiple probs, it wasn't clear what was 'clickable' and often no real logic to where one should click; later puzzles don't seem to follow logic as earlier ones do and seem hard for the sake of it; lastly, trying to be clever by having you 'complete' the game and expect the player to know to restart the game and theoretically 'reset all progress'' in order to access part 2 is actually dumb. Shame.
Amazing game!!!!!!
Very good game, the puzzles are worth the money & the illustrations are fun & quirky. The added bonus is once you've finished the game new features are added to the second time you play it.
This game is an art, this game is my dream, this game is perfect
Loved it!
Fun puzzler and good time killer.
Fun game and interesting storyline

I liked what this game has to offer in terms of puzzles. Good exercise for modest times and form part of a rather simplistic yet, a plausible plotline. However, its not entertaining neither interesting enough to keep one wanting to returning. It could do wonders for a younger audience but, many matured people would rather find it dull (SPOILERS) esp. when repeating the same puzzles after the first round is over. It's not a waste of money, but certainly not worth it.
Game is just amazing. I play quest games since 1991 and this one is on the top of my favorite games list.
Brilliant game! Make sure when you finish you restart and get the second version!
Most of it is good

Good but flawed or glitchy(?). Loved the style of the game, however I.e. the number in the bottle shows as 19581216 when according to online cheat it should state 201102, which is a clue I looked for in vain.
Kind of difficult to follow the story. Felt lost a times. But you're also lost on an island. So maybe it's just part of the game love the graphics.
Loved it
Beautiful graphics, awesome soundtrack. Puzzles are just the right difficulty. Dialogues are witty, the island setting is mesmerizing. Overall ‚ù§Ô∏è, MUST PLAY!

Similar to the Rusty Lake games but more surreal and less creepy. As with the original Isoland, you must play through completely to get the "real" ending--a gimmick I personally don't like but at least was ready for this time.

Excellent! I'm a huge fan of the rusty Lake escape games, Haiku games, Fran bow, dropsy, and all of those amazing escape room type games. This one tends to be a little trickier than the aforementioned because if there is like an open world type environment with a ton of different clothes and a ton of different puzzles and it is up to you to figure out when the solutions actually have to come and play. I have found that taking notes on the clues as you play has been a great help!
Awesome. Old school puzzle. Have been looking for a new mobile game for months. Found it!

Strange graphical weirdness with sides of screen, suspect no support for wide displays. Also highly irritating bar moving across the screen from left to right constantly. Not a fan of paid hints when having already purchased app. Unfortunately uninstalled within minutes and will not consider other apps by dev especially as this is no longer supported so represents how they consider an app finished.

Enjoyable graphics but rather short for what it is, puzzles often didn't take much thinking at all. Others were a bit more involved which was more enjoyable. Some were just plainly handed over by NPCs
Obscure puzzles that don't make sense

I can't give more than one star because any merits of the game are destroyed by the greediness of the devs. Even though you buy the game you have to watch videos to get hints which are often not much help at all. This is pure greed. If you choose to buy the game you shouldn't have to keep paying in app purchases. For that reason it is an instant uninstall and I certainly wont play any other games by this developer. A real shame.
Very fun game with challenging puzzles.
Pay for hints or watch ads. No thank you, not after initially purchasing the game.
Fun to play. No bugs. A bit short but the price is low anyway.

4 stars to encourage the devs, an overall enjoyable experience, but couple of things I didn't like: Ads for vague hints /more money for detailed hints (which I didn't try), what what the heck with the red box which I didn't open in the end (??), plot had promise but didn't really explain anything, and I got stuck because I didn't click behind the statue. Beyond that, I didn't need hints for the puzzles, so it was doable. I think that the concept of the 2nd play seemed unnecessary...?
Keeps freezing, uninstalled

Decent game, but a little short. Most of the puzzles are fairly easy but the last few are extremely difficult, which feels unbalanced. Since there is no ability to take photos or notes, you need to rely heavily on your device's screenshot functionality during the final stages. There are also a couple of occasions where there are places to navigate which lack the "arrow" and so these are incredibly difficult to find. It was fun, but a camera feature and better navigation is definitely needed.
Quite enjoyable, but Round 2 got boring.
Loved this game, so original.
Really enjoyed the puzzles

Four stars for the first playthrough, but two stars for requiring a second, mostly identical playthrough to get the real ending. Second time through I didn't look at a poster that has a very obvious clue to an easy puzzle, but it turns out second time through, the poster (which looks the same until you zoom in on it) has new, critical info on it.

Paid for the premium version and they still want to charge you for tips or you can watch a video. If I was willing to watch videos I wouldn't of paid for the premium version. Deleted the app, black balling the developers.
Brilliant
it's ok
beautiful and mysterious, good puzzles, gorgeous music.

Enjoyed the puzzles. Success without looking at hints requires awareness of the environment. Solution to puzzles are literally written on the walls. While it would help to highlight which items in the environment can be picked up, assume to click on anything new at least once. In agreement with a critical reviewer that the "plant" item was weak.

This is the kind of game that I like and I enjoyed it thoroughly. The puzzles were just the right difficulty for me. Had to think but not too much. I had to consult a walkthrough a few times. The graphics were cool and gave the game a certain ambience that I liked. My only criticism is that to get a hint in the game you have to watch a silly ad. Would rather pay more and have ad free hints.

Very challenging and kept my interest the whole way! Great game... Especially if you like puzzles that require some thought. This game would be 5 stars if the people who couldn't solve the puzzles would stop blaming the game for their own inadequacies.

Great game! Excellent mixture of easy and hard puzzles, as well as some very subtle clues and surprising, accidental finds. I finally managed to get all the achievements and I can hardly wait to to try the sequel, Ashes of Time. Well worth the cost.

Puzzles weren't too hard, what's harder finding some of the clues, and discovering that you have to talk to the characters to get things rolling. Bonus game was good too, though a little disconcerting to have to hit "new game" to get there. I don't usually buy games from an author with no previous work to sample free, but I'm glad I took the gamble.
fun art and fun puzzles

there's so much to appreciate about this game. i love that you have to really think outside the box in order to solve puzzles. sure it makes for higher difficulty of play but that's what I want out of a game! graphics and style was awesome and overall very fluid game play.
Way too hard
It's a very fun game, but some parts are quite difficult. Graphic is awesome as a puzzle game.
Quite absorbing, sometimes frustrating

Awesome fun game with challenges all the way, the graphics, and there colours were rather fun to look at and unique, sound and music excellent too, it all had a French holiday resort feeling to it, I can't fault Isoland, it was superb, I was sorry when I eventually completed it. Top game CottonGame, please bring us Isoland 2.
beautiful graphic, plenty of more than decent puzzles. just too short. I could play that for days. perfect game!
An ok point and click game.

if you want to complete game isoland 1, you must buy isoland 2..

One of the worst games I've attempted to play! Cartoons are nice, but trying to solve the puzzles is impossible. Extremely frustrating & gets very boring, very quickly. Don't waste your time and money.

Weird, but wonderful! Strange little game, where nothing seems obvious. Funny cartoon characters talking nonsense (mostly) and crazy graphics make this a unique puzzle game. Didn't really understand much of it, but was glad to get all the achievements.
Great indie point and click adventure

Unique graphic style, ambient music and thoughtful puzzler. To get the full 
benefit of the game you need to play it through a second time for the real 
challenge. For clues you need to be very observant, background detail might 
not just be there to look appealing but holds clues. Bargain price for it 
and though some have criticized Isoland for clue charging. If you're 
struggling on the basics, perhaps this isn't for you, but hey! That's what 
YouTube is for! Can't wait to get into part 2! üòÄ

Very enjoyable and tricky. The initial completion of the game demanded a 
second try as not all the puzzles where completed. I got to the end of the 
game but not to the "truth". The puzzles are harder as you progress deeper 
in the game.

Great adventure game, I loved the graphics/design and ingenious puzzles 
that required attention to details of the game and were not too obvious as 
is case of many adventures today.

Amazing point and click game. Reminded me of the broken sword games of back 
in the day. Can't wait for the 3rd one to come.

I really wanted to like this game but it's absolutely a huge 
disappointment. The art style is nice, the music is okay but repetitive. 
The problem is the game isn't really intuitive. The puzzles really don't 
jump out at you and the art style prevents you from finding points of 
interest on generic screens.

Nice art but I'm disgusted that I paid for it but am being told to pay 
another dollar to unlock hints. Just charge the buck at the gate. Super 
grimy tactic. Yes it's just a dollar but it's the principle. Seriously.
Very good game, music, graphic and mystery. Love it

I then tried to purchase a hint and that too froze the game with no hint given. I'm stuck, can't progress and am annoyed that the game is busted after I have rather enjoyed the puzzles so far.

I liked it, definitely worth a buck. My only issue is that the game crashes any time I try to do anything else on my phone. Really annoying when I want to play in between replying to messages, or when I need to check a walkthrough for a difficult puzzle.

Fun game but the problems are: 1, the clicking is kind of responsive. And 2, the game crashes if i exit the game by clicking home button, clicking a notification, watching a video or phone goes to sleep.

A fun game. Short, but reflected in the price, which is fine.  Challenging puzzles that are ultimately solvable, especially if you use pen and paper. Beautiful graphics and art style. I rated it 4/5 because I felt like the plot was ultimately unsatisfying and I didn't really understand the ending. A bit too surreal for my liking.

Memorably offbeat visuals and audio. Puzzles are all logically deductible and enjoyably challenging. I'm rating 5 stars because I like to support new creators, but the reliance on obscure mythos in place of storytelling, and the relative lack of puzzle variety would make it 4 stars from an established developer.
Ohhhhhh this game is amazing but unfortunately it would be better if there were more than 2 rounds ( My English not very good)

Great price, awesome game. Love the quirky style.

This game lacks a plot, therefore it's hard to know what's next. There is no easy way to know shay puzzle to play next, especially that you have to go from one location to the other multiple times. Also, there is a lot memorizing in this game. If you don't have a pen and paper, you'll be lost. Feels like you're doing homework instead.
Fun puzzle game! Definitely worth it!

Click a plant three times to get a key. Why? Because otherwise they couldn't make you watch an ad to get the clue.

Isoland is wonderfully weird and looks fabulous. The design is simple and slick - it doesn't take long to navigate around the map or use objects in the inventory. The puzzles are reasonably easy, so I doubt anyone will get frustrated for long, but if you're after a serious mental challenge you might be disappointed. It does help to have a piece of paper handy! I wish it had been longer, but it's easily worth the (very cheap) price.
Too easy, but more then decent for its price
